ns,we'll kick the winning score,you'll hear our mighty roar!;/poem;;/blockquote;Awards and achievementsTeam* '''AFL Grand Final Appearances''': '''Premierships''': 3 (2001, 2002, 2003): '''Runners-up''': 1 (2004)* '''Pre-Season Grand Final Appearances''': '''Premierships''': 1 (2013): '''Runners-up:''' 2 (2001, 2007)* '''(Reserves) North East Australian Football League Premierships''': '''Premierships''': 3 (2001, 2012, 2013)* '''Wooden Spoons''': 1 (1998)IndividualList of Brisbane Lions individual awards and recordsClub facts'''Premierships'''*2001*2002*2003'''Runners Up'''*2004'''Coaches'''* John Northey: 1997–1998* Roger Merrett: 1998 (caretaker)* Leigh Matthews: 1999–2008* John Blakey: 2005 (caretaker)* Michael Voss: 2009–2013* Mark Harvey: 2013 (caretaker)* Justin Leppitsch: 2014–'''Captains'''* Michael Voss (co-captain: 1997–2000; captain: 2000–2006)* Alastair Lynch (co-captain: 1997–2000)* Chris Johnson (co-captain: 2007)* Nigel Lappin (co-captain: 2007–2008)* Simon Black (co-captain: 2007–2008)* Luke Power (co-captain: 2007–2008)* Jonathan Brown (co-captain: 2007–2008, 2013; captain: 2009–2012)* Jed Adcock (co-captain: 2013; captain: 2014)* Tom Rockliff (captain: 2015–present)'''Biggest home crowds'''{| class="wikitable sortable"|- style="background:#bdb76b;"! Rank !! Crowd !! Round, Season !! Result !! Opponent !! Brisbane Lions !! Opposition !! Margin !! Venue !! Day/Night/Twilight|-|1|| 37,224 || 15, 2005 || Win ||  || 19.19 (133) || 7.13 (55) || +78 || The Gabba || Night|-|2|| 37,032 || PF2, 2001 || Win ||  || 20.16 (136) || 10.8 (68) || +68 || The Gabba || Night|-|3|| 36,803 || 4, 2003 || Win || Collingwood || 14.11 (95) || 11.15 (81) || +14 || The Gabba || Night|-|4|| 36,780 || 2, 2010 || Win || Carlton || 16.11 (107) || 12.16 (88) || +19 || The Gabba || Night|-|5|| 36,467 || 3, 2004 || Win || Collingwood || 21.11 (137) || 12.5 (77) || +60 || The Gabba || Night|-|6|| 36,197 || 1, 2003 || Win ||  || 14.20 (104) || 8.13 (61) || +43 || The Gabba || Night|