 team's secondary training venue Giffin Park in Coorparoo, a four-minute drive from the Gabba.Reserves premierships{| class="wikitable"|style="text-align: center;" colspan="6"|'''Premierships (3)'''|-!Year!Competition!Opponent!Score!Venue|-| 2001 || QAFL|| Southport Sharks ||  '''13.20 (98) – 13.8 (86)''' || Giffin Park|-| 2012 || NEAFL|| Queanbeyan Tigers ||  '''22.12 (144) – 11.9 (75)''' || Manuka Oval|-| 2013 || NEAFL|| Sydney Swans ||  '''12.9 (81) – 10.13 (73)''' || Graham Rd Oval|}Season summaries{| class="wikitable"|- style="background:#bdb76b;"! Season !! Win–Loss–Draw !! Ladder position !! Finals result|-| 2011 || 4–13–1 || 10th (Wooden spoon) || DNQ|-| 2012 || 14–4–0 || 2nd || '''Premiers'''|-| 2013 || 16–2–0 || 1st (Minor premiership) || '''Premiers'''|-| 2014 || 6–12–0 || 9th || DNQ|-| 2015 || 2–16–0 || 10th || DNQ|}See alsoBrisbane* Wikipedia listing of Brisbane Lions players* Merrett–Murray Medal* Australian rules football in Queensland* Sport in Queensland* Sport in AustraliaNotes;ReferencesExternal linksBrisbane Lions